Anti-War Movements<br><br>
   Does anyone have any information on anti-war movements<br>
among the North Vietnamese?  How would the Hanoi government<br>
have handled anti-war demonstrations?  Americans were free<br>
to demonstrate against the war, and I even saw South Vietnamese demonstrations against the war in 1971.  Why were there none reported from the North although the losses among the young men from the North were greater than among Americans or any of their allies, with the possible exception of the South Vietnamese?<br>
   Another question comes to mind.  If the sincere demonstrators realized that the government was responsible for the war, why did they not spit on their senators instead of the veterans?<br>

